it on Dark\nMatter pair annihilation cross section from gamma-ray surveys of Ursa Minor. At\nthe same time, if one goes back to a fixed trial parametric form for the\ndensity, e.g. using a NFW or Burkert profile, we show that the minimal $J$ can\nhardly be reduced by more than a factor of 1.5.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 24 Mar 2016 19:52:23 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 15 Jul 2016 14:04:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-07-26"}
